---

<div
  id="termsModal"
  class="fixed inset-0 z-[100] hidden bg-ink/85 backdrop-blur-sm"
  role="dialog"
  aria-modal="true"
  aria-labelledby="termsModalTitle"
>
  <div
    class="mx-auto my-[7.5vh] w-[min(90vw,48rem)] max-w-3xl max-h-[85vh] flex flex-col overflow-hidden bg-ink-2 border border-ink-3 rounded-xl transition-[opacity,transform] duration-300 ease-out-quart"
  >
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between px-8 py-6 border-b border-ink-3">
      <h2 id="termsModalTitle" class="font-display font-bold text-paper text-xl tracking-[-0.01em]">
        Terms of Service
      </h2>
      <button
        id="closeTermsModal"
        type="button"
        aria-label="Close"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-11 h-11 text-paper-2 hover:text-cobalt-3 transition-colors duration-200"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"></line>
          <line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"></line>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- Body -->
    <div class="flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-8 py-6 modal-legal">
      <p class="font-body text-paper-2 leading-[1.7] mb-4">Please review our terms of service carefully.</p>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-paper-2 mb-8">
        LAST UPDATED &middot; JANUARY 15, 2025
      </p>

      <section>
        <h3>AGREEMENT TO TERMS</h3>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") are a legally binding agreement between you ("you" or "user"),
          whether personally or on behalf of an organization, and Pacebeats ("Company," "we," "our," or "us"),
          governing your access to and use of the Pacebeats mobile application and any related platforms,
          services, or tools (collectively, the "Service").
        </p>
        <p>
          By downloading, accessing, or using our Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
          If you do not agree, you must immediately stop using the Service and uninstall the application.
        </p>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms at any time, and the updated version will be indicated by a "Last Updated" date.
          Your continued use of the Service after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of those changes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>1. Acceptance of Terms</h3>
        <p>
          By accessing and using Pacebeats, you accept and agree to be bound by the terms and provisions
          of this agreement. This includes all policies, guidelines, and rules referenced herein.
          Your continued use of the service constitutes acceptance of any modifications to these terms.
          If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>2. Use License and Restrictions</h3>
        <p>
          Permission is granted to use Pacebeats for personal, non-commercial fitness and running purposes only.
          This license does not include modifying or copying our materials, using the materials for commercial purposes,
          attempting to reverse engineer any software contained in Pacebeats, removing any copyright or proprietary notations,
          or transferring the materials to another person or mirroring the materials on any other server.
          This license shall automatically terminate if you violate any of these restrictions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>3. User Account Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>
          You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities
          that occur under your account. This includes creating a strong password and keeping it secure,
          not sharing your account credentials with others, promptly notifying us of any unauthorized access
          or security breaches, ensuring your account information remains accurate and up-to-date,
          and understanding that you are responsible for any content posted or actions taken through your account.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>4. Data Privacy and Protection</h3>
        <p>
          Pacebeats is committed to protecting your personal information while providing the best possible
          fitness tracking experience. Our data protection practices include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Secure encryption of all personal data and fitness metrics</li>
          <li>Limited data collection only for app functionality improvement</li>
          <li>No sharing of personal information with third parties without consent</li>
          <li>User control over data sharing and deletion</li>
          <li>Compliance with applicable data protection regulations</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>5. Health and Safety Disclaimer</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Pacebeats is a fitness tracking application and should not be used as a substitute
          for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. By using this app:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>You acknowledge that you are physically capable of participating in running activities</li>
          <li>You understand the risks associated with physical exercise and running</li>
          <li>You agree to consult with a healthcare professional before beginning any new fitness routine</li>
          <li>You will not hold Pacebeats liable for any injuries or health issues that may occur</li>
          <li>You will use the app responsibly and within your physical limitations</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h3>6. Music and Content Usage</h3>
        <p>
          Pacebeats integrates with music streaming services to provide tempo-matched playlists.
          Users are responsible for having valid subscriptions to any third-party music services.
          We do not store or distribute copyrighted music content. All music is streamed through
          legitimate platforms in accordance with their respective terms of service.
